I might have made some mistakes w/ syntax, but you should get the general idea...
[code:39v9wpvh]if %score% &lt; 20 then msg &lt;Text here&gt;
if %score% &lt; 40 AND %score% &gt; 20 then msg &lt;Text here&gt;
if %score% &lt; 60 AND %score% &gt; 40 then msg &lt;Text here&gt;
[/code:39v9wpvh]

However, nothing happens if %score% is exactly 20, 40, or 60.  To fix this this code would work:[code:39v9wpvh]if %score% &lt;= 20 then msg &lt;Text here&gt;
if %score% &lt;= 40 AND %score% &gt; 20 then msg &lt;Text here&gt;
if %score% &lt;= 60 AND %score% &gt; 40 then msg &lt;Text here&gt;
[/code:39v9wpvh]


Also, you have nothing for if score is above 60.

if ( %money% &lt;= 0 ) then msg &lt;You do not have enough gold&gt;

or if u wanted to buy something for 200 gold, and u only had 150 gold...

if ( %money% &lt; 200 ) then msg &lt;You do not have enough gold&gt;

if using QDK, use condition scripts.
